answer:
It is not recommended that anyone receive more than one dose of influenza vaccine in a season, except for children under 9 years of age who have never had a seasonal influenza vaccine for whom two doses are recommended. If you have further questions, please speak with your health care provider. 
You can find more information on influenza vaccines, including Fluzone® High-Dose, here. 
Immunization Nurse
